{"title":"The 2025 Paul Component x Falconer Cycles Sierra Trailblazer","link":"https://theradavist.com/the-2025-paul-component-x-falconer-cycles-sierra-trailblazer/","date":1744247843000,"content":"<p><em>This is the 8<sup>th</sup> year in a row that <a href=\"https://sierranevada.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sierra Nevada Brewing</a> asked <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/paul-component-engineering/\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Component Engineering</a> to build them a custom one-off bike, the Sierra Trailblazer, to show at <a href=\"https://www.seaotterclassic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sea Otter Classic</a> in Monterey, then give it away to raise money for a non-profit. Let’s take a look below!</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-8.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This year, the Chico, California-based manufacturer built the “Sierra Trailblazer”, a Falconer Cycles frame outfitted with American-made parts from Paul Component, White Industries, Velocity, BTCHN’ Bikes, King Cage, and more.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-19.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-19.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-18.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-18.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-16.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-16.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The crackled “burned” paint job and shiny new “Pale Ale” green anodized components represent fire and new growth, a phoenix rising from the ashes of the Dixie Fire that burned 1 million acres in the northern Sierra in 2021. The frame is handcrafted by Cameron Falconer, based in Quincy, California, where the fire occurred.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-6.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-6.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-20.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-20.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>In a true component manufacturer collaborative effort, Fox generously donated their hot new fork and dropper post, and SRAM outfitted it with the just-released cable-actuated Transmission drivetrain, making this the ultimate Lost Sierra hardtail.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-3.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-3.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-13.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-13.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-13.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-13.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>You can donate <span>to <a href=\"https://sierratrails.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sierra Buttes Trail Stewardship</a>,  an organization building and maintaining trails in Plumas and Sierra counties, where the Dixie Fire burned, in person at Sea Otter or on the Donation Page until April 24th for a chance to win this bike</span>.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-11.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-11.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-4.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-15.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-15.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>When fire crews used trails on Mount Hough (a trail network SBTS has extensively built for the past decade) as access points to fight the fire, it caused SBTS to reexamine the role recreational trails can play in forest management and economic recovery. Resulting in the development of a revolutionary new concept called Fire Hardened Trails.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Paul_Component_Falconer_Sierra_Trailblazer-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This involves prescribing new trailbuilding projects to reduce ground and ladder fuels, create healthier forests, and protect local communities. Patagonia highlighted this concept in its recent film, <a href=\"https://www.patagonia.com/stories/fire-lines/video-153372.html\">Fire Lines</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Build Spec:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Custom Hardtail Frame by <a href=\"https://falconercycles.com/\">Falconer Cycles</a> size “Medium”</li>\n<li>Brakes, Levers, Stem, Dropper Trigger, and Seatcollar by <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\">PAUL Component</a></li>\n<li>Cranks, Chainring, Bottom Bracket, Headset, and Hubs by <a href=\"https://www.whiteind.com/\">White Industries</a></li>\n<li>Rims by <a href=\"https://www.velocityusa.com/home/\">Velocity USA</a></li>\n<li>Titanium Bottle Cages by <a href=\"https://kingcage.com/\">King Cage</a></li>\n<li>Custom Anodized Titanium Handlebar by <a href=\"https://www.btchnbikes.com/\">BTCHN Bikes</a></li>\n<li>Cablehousing by <a href=\"https://www.sim.works/\">Simworks</a></li>\n<li>Saddle, Grips, Tires, and Sealant by <a href=\"https://www.wtb.com/\">WTB</a></li>\n<li>Superleggera Fork and Transfer Dropper Post by <a href=\"https://ridefox.com/pages/bike\">Fox Bike</a></li>\n<li>Cable Actuated Transmission Shifters, Derailleur, Chain, and Cassette by <a href=\"https://www.sram.com/en/sram\">SRAM</a></li>\n<li>CNC Cable tips by <a href=\"https://foragercycles.com/\">Forager Cycles</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://givebutter.com/trailblazer\" target=\"_blank\">Donate for your chance to win at the Sierra Buttes Trail Stewardship</a>!</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/the-2025-paul-component-x-falconer-cycles-sierra-trailblazer/\">The 2025 Paul Component x Falconer Cycles Sierra Trailblazer</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"fb96e2c341ebdb701d015d05053e9e3774d4e889372b5d0576140eead107eb4f","category":"Cycling"}